<p>The <code>tag</code> function wraps a value as a PAD tag (wraps in braces).</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'myTag' | tag{close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{echo 'myTag' | tag}</b></p>

<h2>Dynamic Tag Names</h2>
{set $tagName = 'users'}
<pre>{open}set $tagName = 'users'{close}
{open}echo $tagName | tag{close}</pre>
<p>Dynamic tag: <b>{echo $tagName | tag}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'IF' | lower | tag{close}</pre>
<p>Lowercase tag: <b>{echo 'IF' | lower | tag}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo 'my_tag' | replace('_', '') | tag{close}</pre>
<p>Clean tag name: <b>{echo 'my_tag' | replace('_', '') | tag}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo 'data' | tag{close}</pre>
<p>Data tag: <b>{echo 'data' | tag}</b></p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>The <code>tag</code> function is useful for dynamically generating PAD tag syntax. It wraps the value in braces.</p>
